The paper focuses on improving the perceptual quality of generated images in GAN-based text-to-image synthesis. This involves optimizing on perceptual loss functions that measure pixel, feature activation, and texture differences against a natural image. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of GANs, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of natural language processing techniques to generate text descriptions, which falls under the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves the generation of images of birds and flowers, which falls under the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics).
